Boil a full #kettle{}. While you wait, halve, peel and 1/4 tsp @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.

Add the @Jasmine Rice{150%g} and cook for ~{12-13%minutes}.

While the rice cooks, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @Diced British Chicken Breast{390%g} and @Echalion Shallot{1}(halved and peeled) to the #pan and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}.

Fry until the chicken is golden brown on the outside and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve the @Sugar Snap Peas{80%g} widthways.

Once the rice is cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

When the chicken is cooked, add the garlic and sugar snaps to the frying pan.

Stir-fry until the sugar snaps are just tender, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir the @Teriyaki Sauce{75%g}, @Sambal Paste{15%g} (add less if you'd prefer things milder), @Water{50%ml} for the sauce and half the @Roasted White Sesame Seeds{5%g} into the pan.

Simmer until slightly thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}, then remove from the heat. Taste and season if needed.

Add a splash more water if you feel it needs it.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and share between your bowls.

Top with the sambal teriyaki chicken stir-fry.

Finish by scattering over the remaining sesame seeds. Enjoy!